OL,3,C'I work endlessly and get nowhere -
OL,4,Csometimes I can't afford to shower'
OL,6,FWhen she became an adult and left
OL,7,Fcare, Chloe only had herself to rely
OL,8,Fon and lacked the family support that
OL,9,Fmany of her peers relied on.
OL,11,FDespite these challenges, Chloe has
OL,12,Fkickstarted her own business - The
OL,13,FDragonfruit Fairies - which sells
OL,14,Fhandcrafted products, runs workshops
OL,15,Fand provides safe-spaces for people.
OL,17,FIt is something she feels she could
OL,18,Fand would have done sooner, if more
OL,19,Fsupport had been available.
